- decisions: FULL demo; LLM runs client-side on WebGPU (WebLLM/Transformers.js) behind an in-browser `LLMRouter` that mirrors the production provider-agnostic backend contract; hero = end-to-end run/review/approve/push loop on Authority + Newsletter engines; Knowledge Engine Lite + console shell as supporting; save/push destinations simulated in-browser by default (real GitHub push only if planner greenlights a blueprint).
- next needs: intake → structured brief.json graded against the requirement + TO-APPLY checklist above; researcher must find Pathwaize's real brand + GHL embed specifics; planner locks bespoke palette/fonts + confirms whether any mw-backend blueprint is warranted.
- risks: WebGPU availability varies by browser (demo must detect + show a graceful fallback / "enable WebGPU" note and ideally a mock-LLM path so reviewers without WebGPU still see the flow); reconciling "frontend must not call LLM directly" with a client-side model must be framed honestly as the swappable-provider #1 (do not misrepresent); model download size/latency on first load — pick a small 4-bit model and show a load progress state.
